; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures RTC and generates a real clock frequency at PC13 port.
;    The purpose of this configuration is only for measuring a real frequency of fRTC.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Configure RTC_TA pin as a RTC_OUT port.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. RTC
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. RTC0 : PC13 (RTC_OUT)
;
; E. Note
;    Must multiply measured frequency by 2.
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; RTC0
; 1. Channel                     : 0 (RTC 0)
;
; 2. Clock                       : [ 0 m l 10 ]
;    Source                      : m (MCCR : Misc Clock)
;    MCCR Source                 : l (LSI : Low Speed Internal Clock - 750KHz)
;    Source Divide               : 10 
;
; 3. Config                      : [ 0 i -meas ]
;    Operation                   : i (Interrupt)
;    Measuring fRTC at PC13 port : N/A
;
; PCU (PC13)
; 1. Port Group                : 2 (PCU Port C)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 2 13 a 7 ]
;    Pin Number                : 13
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 7 (RTC_TAMP1)
;
; PCU (PC13)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 2 13 a 7'
mpause 30

sendln 'cm rtc'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 m l 10'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i -meas'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
